\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That… was a good argument, actually.
 Zorian had nothing to say to that.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And then there is him," said Panaxeth, suddenly pointing towards Zach.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Me?" Zach protested.
 "I'm just sitting here quietly, listening to you two talk.
 What about me?"

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I am heavily restricted in regards to the Controller and cannot speak about
 things freely, but I can tell you this – no matter what you think about that
 person, no matter how friendly he seems, you are ultimately enemies.
 In the end, one has to kill the other."

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"That's… That's bullshit!" Zach exploded.
 "What the hell do you mean by that!?"

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"He is good at pretending," Panaxeth said, not even bothering to look at him.
 "However, you should have noticed the signs by now.
 Don't let your emotions overpower your reason."

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Angry and ignored, Zach tried to ram himself into Panaxeth's form, even though
 he knew no fighting was possible here and that this was probably a bad idea.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Panaxeth's form simply blurred for a moment, causing Zach to harmlessly pass
 through it.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I have said all I that needs to be said," Panaxeth said.
 "Make the right choice, Zorian.
 You have until the end of the restart to make a decision.
 I will be waiting."

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then they were outside, back in their real bodies.
 They hadn't even activated the exit function in their marker – it was another
 thing that the primordial could apparently do on its own initiative.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Damn it, damn it, damn it!" Zach raged, throwing around everything in the
 vicinity to vent his frustration.
 Zorian winced when one of the sensitive instruments that the facility staff
 user to study the Sovereign Gate impacted the nearby wall and broke apart.
 That was going to be a real bitch to explain to Krantin.
 "Damn it all to hell! Why is everything suddenly going so 

\emph on

wrong

\emph default

!?"

